OL,4,CFurloughed part-timers 'clinging on to
OL,5,Cdisappearing jobs'
OL,6, Amanda Bellwood, a part-time worker,
OL,7, has been on furlough since the UK's
OL,8, first coronavirus lockdown and fears
OL,9, she will never return to the company
OL,10, where she has worked for 20 years.
OL,12,FThe 57-year-old, who is not using her
OL,13,Freal name, says she is "certain" she'll
OL,14,Fbe made redundant in July, when the
OL,15,Fgovernment will reduce the proportion
OL,16,Fof people's wages it pays to 70% and
OL,17,Femployers will have to pay 10% for
OL,18,Fhours not worked.
